---
const faqEntries = [
  {
    question: "Is this just an app blocker?",
    answer:
      "No. App limits are one tool inside the flow. The point is follow-through: one written plan, pressure that matches the plan, and a proof-based way to clear it.",
  },
  {
    question: "Can I just tap complete or ignore the limit for today?",
    answer:
      "Not in the normal flow. There is no casual bypass: the plan stays active until proof review passes or a real justification is accepted. If what you submit is clear and truthful, the review can be quick. If the proof is weak, the app does not let it through.",
  },
  {
    question: "What stays local?",
    answer:
      "The core PlanKept flow is designed to stay on your device. That includes plan text, proof-review inputs, submitted photos, and AI conversations used inside the app. Device permissions and sources like Apple Health or Screen Time are also handled on device.",
  },
  {
    question: "Can it use real signals from my life?",
    answer:
      "Yes, when the plan calls for it and you allow it. Proof review can inspect signals like Apple Health step counts or current Screen Time state, and it can validate submitted photos, to help decide whether the plan was actually completed.",
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="landing-section">
  <div class="landing-section__inner">
    <div class="section-heading" data-reveal>
      <p class="section-kicker">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">The important questions are practical ones.</h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        This page should make the product feel clear, not mysterious. Here are the parts that
        usually matter most.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="plan-kept-faq-list">
      {faqEntries.map((entry, index) => (
        <details class="plan-kept-faq landing-surface" data-faq-item data-reveal>
          <summary
            class="plan-kept-faq__button"
            id={`plan-kept-faq-${index + 1}-button`}
            data-faq-trigger
          >
            <span class="plan-kept-faq__question">{entry.question}</span>
            <span class="plan-kept-faq__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="plan-kept-faq__content" data-faq-content>
            <div
              class="plan-kept-faq__panel"
              id={`plan-kept-faq-${index + 1}-panel`}
              role="region"
              aria-labelledby={`plan-kept-faq-${index + 1}-button`}
            >
              <p class="plan-kept-faq__answer">{entry.answer}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
